article.headline: SE Louisiana 70, Southern U. 59
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- Daryl Cohen scored 19 points to lead three players in double figures as Southeastern Louisiana scored the first seven points of the game and cruised past Southern University 70-59 on Wednesday. Terry Bryant added 14 points and seven assists for Southeastern (6-4) while Quennell Green had 13 as the Lions shot a season-high 52 percent from the floor and forced 20 turnovers. Southern, the defending SWAC champions, fell to 0-10 on the season. Cohen, who was 1-for-11 in an 88-62 loss at Florida State on Sunday, went 7-for-14 from the floor against the Jaguars and opened the game with a 3-pointer before a pair of baskets by Green gave Southeastern a 7-0 lead. The Lions increased their lead to 21-3 after a 3-pointer by Dekyron Nicks before Southern went to its bench and chipped away at the lead. Southern closed to 29-23 with 2:09 left in the first half on a bucket by Mariun Price before Southeastern scored the final eight points, including a tip-in by Joseph Polite at the buzzer for a 37-23 halftime lead. Southeastern opened the second half on another 7-0 run as Green hit a baseline jumper, Cohen drained a 3-pointer and Bryant hit a jumper in the lane to take a 44-23 lead. The Jaguars, who were led by Steffon Wiley and Douglas Scott with 12 points each, closed to within 11 points on two occasions in the final minute but could get no closer. Polite, who pulled down a season-high 10 rebounds for Southeastern, blocked a career-high four shots for the Lions as they held Southern to 39 percent shooting from the floor.
